  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Men with Klinefelter syndrome undergo unilateral subcapsular ochiectomy, and the removed
      testicular tissue is examined for presence of sperm and cryopreserved in small pieces for
      fertility treatment and scientific purposes. Prior to operation blood samples are frozen in a
      biobank.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
